                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "Requirements analysts and their clients use requirements to explain their understanding of how the system should behave. Designers treat requirements as constraints on what would be considered an acceptable solution. The test team derives from the requirements a suite of acceptance tests , which will be used to demonstrate to the customer that the system being delivered is indeed what was ordered. The maintenance team uses the requirements to help ensure that system enhancements (repairs and new features) do not interfere with the system's original intent.",
