    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "Types of testing that address verification include function tests and performance tests, which check that the integrated system performs its functions as specified and meets nonfunctional system requirements such as security, accuracy, speed, and reliability.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
