    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "Icons make system functions clear and easy to understand, allowing users to select functions by clicking on icons rather than recalling commands and syntax, which simplifies training for novice users.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "A system can be designed so that its interface with the user makes system functions clear and easy to understand. Most computer-based systems follow the example of Apple and Xerox in using icons to depict a user's choice of system functions. A click of the mouse selects an icon, and a second click invokes the function. Training for such systems is relatively simple, since the functions are more easily remembered by scanning the icons than by recalling commands and syntax.",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ]
    },
    {
