    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "Training for infrequent users differs from standard user training because infrequent users may forget system functions not exercised regularly. For instance, a corporate president who uses a word processing system only once or twice a week needs training focused on basic document creation and modification, unlike typists who use the system daily and require more comprehensive training.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "Training for an infrequent user is different from standard user training. The president has no need to know all the special features of the system; training for infrequent users can address only basic document creation and modification functions.",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "Similarly, specialized training courses can be designed for users with special needs, such as those who need to create charts and reports versus those who only need to access existing ones.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "Similarly, specialized training courses can be designed for those who have special needs. If a system produces charts and reports, some users may need to know how to create the charts and reports, whereas others only want to access existing ones.",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "Documentation also varies by audience; for example, an analyst requires a system overview with computing details not relevant to a user, and operator documentation includes descriptions unimportant to users.",
