[
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "Maintenance research addresses several key problems including predicting likely sources of faults, measuring maintainability based on product information, and developing models to show interconnections among products, processes, and resources.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "Maintenance is a ripe area of research. Many of our maintenance activities could be made easier or more effective if we were better at predicting the likely sources of faults. Researchers are looking for better ways to measure maintainability based on product information; they are developing new models to show us the interconnections among products, processes, and resources.",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "Research also focuses on estimating the effort needed to maintain a system and determining when it is appropriate to retire or rejuvenate legacy systems.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "Similarly, the models will help us know how much effort is needed to maintain a system and when it is appropriate to retire a legacy system or rejuvenate it.",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "Another area of research is the development of tools to assist in the maintenance process, including reengineering tools, change control and configuration management repositories, and project history databases.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "Work continues on building tools to assist us in the maintenance process. Reengineering tools, change control and configuration management repositories, and project history databases are likely to become more sophisticated as researchers build prototypes based on empirical data.",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "Researchers are also interested in general laws of software maintenance to understand whether software system evolution behavior is consistent and predictable.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
                "content": "Finally, researchers will continue to look at general laws of software maintenance, as suggested by Lehman (1980).They are eager to learn whether software engineering theory can confirm what empirical observation indicates in practice: namely, that the behavior of software systems evolution is consistent and predictable.",
                "img_id": null
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "role": "paragraph",
        "segment": "Conferences such as the International Conference on Software Maintenance (ICSM) and journals like Software Maintenance: Research and Practice are dedicated to these maintenance issues.",
        "citations": [
            {
                "type": "source_text",
